1991 saw the release of the first - of numerous - hits compilations with Jennifer Rush; "The Power Of Jennifer Rush". The thirteen track set not only omitted several of Rush's singles, like "Come Give Me Your Hand", "Into My Dreams", "Wings Of Desire" and "Love Get Ready", but somewhat peculiarly closed with the Spanish language versions of the two biggest hits from 1988's Passion; "You're My One And Only" and "Keep All The Fires Burning Bright". Included as 'bonus tracks' here are consequently not only those singles but also the 12" mixes of all of Rush's greatest hits - plus the Spanish versions of "If You're Ever Gonna Lose My Love" and "The Power Of Love".
